(80, 1, '2014-03-24 21:49:26', '2014-03-24 21:49:26', 'The Bristol Bronies, the UK''s most spectacularly Bristol-based brony meet organisation, is holding a My Little Pony season three premiere! Come one, come all! Come and witness the amazing magic of the great and powerful<del>Trixie</del>season three!\r\n<h2>Say what now?</h2>\r\nSeason Three of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic has been announced to begin on<strong>Saturday November 10th</strong>with a double-episode feature. The time, although rumoured to be around 3pm GMT, has not yet been confirmed. We plan to hire out a sweet little venue and watch the Crystal Kingdom unfold.\r\n\r\nAs per all Bristol meets,<strong>we are meeting at the Temple Quay Starbucks between 11am and midday</strong>. Due to the late start of the episode, we may be procuring food before moving onto the venue.\r\n\r\n<strong>The venue is<a href="http://hydrabooks.org/">Hydra Books</a>on Old Market.</strong>This is the same place that the season two finale meet was held back in April, unfortunately some of the more "extravagant" venues queried were unavailable at such short notice. As in April, Hydra has a<strong>seated capacity of 35 people</strong>. An RSVP list has been<a href="http://ukofequestria.co.uk/posts/230061/">started on the UK of Equestria thread for this meet</a>on a first come, first served basis - be sure to get your name in there. In the circumstance that there are more attendees than there is room, those who have RSVP''d will be given preference.\r\n\r\nEither way, I''m hope you''re ready for more\r\n<strong>PONIES.</strong>', 'PONIES.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ponies', '', '', '2014-03-24 21:49:26', '2014-03-24 21:49:26', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=meet&#038;p=80', 0, 'meet', '', 0),
