(171, 1, '2014-03-25 10:19:45', '2014-03-25 10:19:45', 'Ominous title aside, this is the last large meet that I (being Grey/Kim/Captain Crunch) will be in charge of. Our upcoming meets will instead be operated by one of our <a href="/about/">several other sexy staff members</a>, starting with Ripp_ in April.\r\n\r\nIt''s been a crazy ride, ponypeople! Let''s hope things''ll only get even better with new folks at the helm!\r\n<h3>Meet plan</h3>\r\n<h4>11:00am12:00pm Starbucks</h4>\r\nWhere we meet.\r\n<h4>12:00am1:30pm The Knight''s Templar</h4>\r\nGrab some pub-grub to go, it''s going to be a long day!\r\n<h4>1:30pm4:30pm Hydra Books</h4>\r\nBack in <del>black</del> books!\r\n<h5>Quiz</h5>\r\nThe extreme quiz of pony-osity rears it''s head once again. Prizes available for the winning team!\r\n<h5>Whose Line Is It Anypony?</h5>\r\nMr WattChimeraHydra will be making his own little twist on this British comedic classic. \r\n<h5>Games Bronies Play</h5>\r\nWe''re talking the <em>My Little Pony CCG</em>, <em>Cards Against Humanity</em>, <em>BUCK: Legacy</em> and more. More games than you can shake a didgeridoo at!\r\n<h5>Episode viewing: For Whom the Sweetie Belle Toils</h5>\r\nYet another episode with the CMCs doing things a little bit wrong for great comedic/moral effect.\r\n<h4>4:30pm6:00pm Forbidden Planet</h4>\r\nBack once again for the renegade master, D4 damager, power to the people. We''ll be collecting our standard array of comics, cards, and crafts. Now featuring the <em>My Little Pony</em> dog tags!\r\n<h4>6:00pm8:00pm Laser Fusion</h4>\r\nThe off-brand name for an activity similar to a <em>quest</em> utilising <em>lasers</em>. Anyway, we''re going to be trying to stick ourselves into Bristol''s downtown arena to make some shooty-shooty action happen!\r\n<h3>Notices</h3>\r\nThere are a few groups due to attend this meet under the umbrella of outside media. This includes Megan Ryder, film student from Cirencester College; Dawn Firth-Godbehere, media and sociology from Goldsmiths, University of London; and Red Cherry Productions, a student production company who are producing an extended version of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nFR9iLHuQqw">their current brony documentary</a>.\r\n\r\nMeet attendees are within their rights to refuse to be filmed or interviewed for any of these. However we cannot guarantee that attendees will not appear in background shots or group photographs.', 'For Whom the Bell Tolls', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'for-whom-the-bell-tolls', '', '', '2014-03-25 10:39:49', '2014-03-25 10:39:49', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=meet&#038;p=171', 0, 'meet', '', 0),
(172, 1, '2014-03-25 10:22:56', '2014-03-25 10:22:56', 'It''s not even started to slow down. There are no brakes on the Bristol Bronies train. This makes it a very dangerous train and that should probably be removed from service until a full safety inspection has been made. But no, the train is still going. The train is us. Train.', 'The Meet Still Hasn''t Ended', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-meet-still-hasnt-ended', '', '', '2014-03-25 10:22:56', '2014-03-25 10:22:56', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=meet&#038;p=172', 0, 'meet', '', 0),
(173, 1, '2014-03-29 07:45:20', '2014-03-29 07:45:20', '(Which is what Grey did since he wanted to use more of our sexy staff members.)\r\n\r\nThis meet marks the 2nd complete year of Bristol brony meetups, counting the Season 2 Finale meet up those 24 months ago.\r\n<h2>MEET PLAN</h2>\r\n<h3>11:00am&ndash;12:00pm Starbucks</h3>\r\nWhere we shall gather to consume enough caffeine<sup>1</sup> to keep us going throughout the day before we move on to...\r\n<h3>12:00am&ndash;1:30pm The Knights Templar</h3>\r\n...The Knights Templar! To grab the food<sup>2</sup> to go with the caffeine<sup>3</sup> to let us get through the craziness<sup>4</sup> of the day that will start with...\r\n<h3>1:30pm&ndash;4:30pm Hydra Books</h3>\r\n...a trip to Hydra books where besides watching the episodes we will enjoy...\r\n<h4>[Figure out things to do at Hydra]</h4>\r\n<h3>4:30pm&ndash;6:00pm Forbidden Planet</h3>\r\n...Forbidden Planet, where you will get the amazing opportunity to spend all your hard earned queen golds<sup>5,6,7</sup> on merchandise for all of the nerdiest things ever.\r\n<h3>[Find an evening activity]</h3>\r\n<div style="font-size: smaller">1: Bristol Bronies doesn''t endorse or encourage the consumption of large quantities of caffeine, or the use of caffeine as a substitute for rest and a balanced diet, please consume caffeine responsibly.\r\n2: Please remember to pay for your food and take only to consume the food you have paid for.\r\n3: There we are referring to Starbucks branded caffeine drank earlier as you are not allowed to drink Starbucks drinks in the pub.<sup>8</sup>\r\n4: Bristol Bronies uses the word "craziness" to mean outside of the norm<sup>9</sup>. We do not endorse the losing of ones mind to a degree where one could be classified as crazy as Screw Loose.\r\n5: Please do not spend more queen golds than you can afford too, remember to stay financially responsible.\r\n6: Please also do not spend other people''s queen golds<sup>7</sup> - That is stealing and it is bad.\r\n7: Queen golds refers to money, specifically British pounds.\r\n8: Nothing however stops you buying more caffeine at the pub and consuming it there with your food.\r\n9: Even though it is only marginally outside the norm to enjoy brightly coloured ponies.</div>', 'Trade ya for the Organizer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'trade-ya-for-the-organizer', '', '', '2014-03-29 07:45:41', '2014-03-29 07:45:41', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=meet&#038;p=173', 0, 'meet', '', 0),
