(178, 1, '2013-06-13 16:52:31', '2013-06-13 16:52:31', 'Well here we are, at the precipice of the worst kept secret ever.\r\n\r\nWelcome, one and all, to the newest iteration of the Bristol Bronies website; rebuilt and redesigned completely from the ground up to be a hell of a lot easier to manage and to hold a hell of a lot more information. Of course, website development never really ends, so consider this a beta and <a href="/contact/">drop us a line</a> if anything goes awry. \r\n\r\nSo, what else can you expect? \r\n\r\n<h3>Prettier pages</h3>\r\nNot only are we running on a whole brand spanking new website (making use of some nifty new HTML and CSS features and some hella large typography), but we now have the ability to customise the designs of individual pages - something we really just badly hacked into the old site when we needed it. Good lord!\r\n\r\n<h3>Consolidated meets</h3>\r\nPast meets and upcoming meets are now combined into a single section, creating one big-ass list meet-y goodness!\r\n\r\n<h3>This thing you''re reading right now</h3>\r\nWe now have a news section. We''re planning to put news in it at some point. \r\n\r\n<h3>Smarter media</h3>\r\nMeet images are now consolidated into <a href="/community/">a single section</a> of the website. Photographs especially have been supercharged, now capable of displaying everything from aperture and exposure information, right down to the place and time where the photo was taken. Videos and text content are due to be added at a later date. \r\n\r\n<h3>Integrated booking</h3>\r\nThe way that our space-limited events used to be managed was that Grey would write your name down in a big list and make sure it didn''t go over a certain number. No more! You can now book your places directly from the website, giving you the peace of mind that it''s on a list that <em>wasn''t</em> written by Grey.\r\n\r\n<h3>Convenient cards</h3>\r\nInformation about meets has been consolidated into <del datetime="2013-06-13T16:25:25+00:00">totally not based on Google</del> cards at the bottom of their relevant pages, sticking all the important information into one easy to find place. And, as always, it''s all marked up and ready for your <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/hcalendar-implementations">hCalendar supporting softwares</a>.\r\n\r\n<h3>Not-just-one-person-doing-everything meet organisation</h3>\r\nMeets can now be added to the site by any approved individual! Multi-user-licious! \r\n\r\n<h3>A freakin'' RSS feed</h3>\r\nA heavily requested feature for nearly as long as we''ve been around, we actually have <a href="/meet/feed/">an RSS feed</a> for meets now (who even uses RSS nowadays, anyway?) \r\n\r\nMore information on what''s going on - what''s up with that logo, anyway? - will be forthcoming soon!', 'Bristol Bronies 3.0', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bristol-bronies-3-0', '', '', '2014-03-25 11:19:53', '2014-03-25 11:19:53', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=news&#038;p=178', 0, 'news', '', 0),
