(181, 1, '2013-06-26 10:00:01', '2013-06-26 10:00:01', 'I <a href="/news/bristol-bronies-3-0/">promised you an explanation</a>, so here it is: Why have we gone and screwed everything up by changing our logo?\r\n\r\nThe Bristol Bronies seal has served us well over the last 12 months - and yes, it has been nearly a whole year since the first version of it appeared. During its entire tenure, apart from the tweaking of some colours, virtually no part of it changed whatsoever. \r\n\r\n<img src="http://bristolbronies.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/bb-logo-first.png" alt="bb-logo-first" width="480" height="313" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-332" />\r\n\r\nOur seal has appeared all over the web, on our posters, cards, badges, in stores, and even <a href="/community/bristol-bronies-cake/">on a cake</a>. But eventually, like all good things it eventually gets a little old and stale (think <em>The Simpsons</em>), and it''s better for it to gracefully retire than for it to be milked for all it''s worth whilst competitors get the upper hand. So that''s what we did. \r\n\r\n<img src="http://bristolbronies.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/brizbronslogo.png" alt="brizbronslogo" width="800" height="397" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-290" />\r\n\r\nThe new logo and brand style is intended to modernise, whilst still harking back to the old. We''re still red, we''re still circular, and we''re still Pinkie Pie; we''re just put on different make-up. \r\n\r\nThe fairly old fashioned concept of the "seal" has been dropped in favour of a minimalist logo which (although admittedly clich) now resembles a speech bubble, putting more emphasis on our role as a social organisation. The previously darker red has been brightened up, making things a little more bright and cheery. The old typeface has lost it''s serifs and bulked up, becoming thick and bold. Our new style depends less on the presence of colour and more on the lack of it, allowing the colourful imagery and prominent text to really stand out. \r\n\r\n<img src="http://bristolbronies.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/cards3b.jpg" alt="cards3b" width="800" height="348" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-313" />\r\n\r\nThe new logo has already been rolled out online and will be on our collectable business cards from <a href="/meet/the-grand-galloping-meet/">this weekend</a>. Badges will be updated in a few months time. ', 'Hitting Refresh', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hitting-refresh', '', '', '2014-03-25 12:01:36', '2014-03-25 12:01:36', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=news&#038;p=181', 0, 'news', '', 0);
