(191, 1, '2013-12-31 19:56:49', '2013-12-31 19:56:49', 'With new years comes a slew of promises for the year ahead. Many of them are specific - to lose weight, to quit smoking, to drink less; ours is simple - to be better. \r\n\r\nA resolution is, of course, meaningless without action, so from tomorrow we''ll be implementing a slew of changes to Bristol Bronies meets and organisation.\r\n\r\n<h2>A monthly modification</h2>\r\n\r\nThe monthly events are seeing the most significant changes. \r\n\r\nMonthly events will now begin at 11am and end at 6pm, a few hours earlier than at current; but wait, there''s more! The evenings will now be dedicated to a different event every month. From bowling to buffets, these optional extras will provide a new dimension to meets, for those who desire a little bit more variety in exchange for a little bit more cost. \r\n\r\nMonthly meets will also now operate on a schedule, running on the penultimate Saturday of every month unless otherwise stated. Hopefully this will mean more consistent spaces between meets, and the ability to plan them well ahead of time. (We can dream, Harold!)\r\n\r\n<h2>An event expansion</h2>\r\n\r\nAs well as changing how monthlies are operated, we are also introducing new meet types and making others (such as the rare "one-shot" meets) more frequent. \r\n\r\nWe are also expanding our borders and plan to hold more events outside of Bristol city centre. Hawaii is unfortunately unlikely.\r\n\r\n<h2>A staff switcharoo</h2>\r\n\r\nMore staff are being taken on board and more meets will be operated by different individuals. \r\n\r\nInternal decision making is also being drastically altered. No longer will Grey serve as your sole lord and saviour, as there will now be three demi-gods who serve as equal leaders of the organisation - deciding once-and-for-all the rules, operations, and just who is best pony. <small>It''s totally Rainbow Dash.</small> \r\n\r\nThe operating policies for social media, finances, competitions, advertising and marketing are all being altered to be more effectively utilised and to better benefit you - the community. \r\n\r\nWe think we''ve had a good year, and hope you''ve had one too. We look forward to seeing you in 2014!', 'Resolutions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'resolutions', '', '', '2014-03-25 12:11:21', '2014-03-25 12:11:21', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=news&#038;p=191', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(192, 1, '2014-03-25 12:11:21', '2014-03-25 12:11:21', 'With new years comes a slew of promises for the year ahead. Many of them are specific - to lose weight, to quit smoking, to drink less; ours is simple - to be better. \r\n\r\nA resolution is, of course, meaningless without action, so from tomorrow we''ll be implementing a slew of changes to Bristol Bronies meets and organisation.\r\n\r\n<h2>A monthly modification</h2>\r\n\r\nThe monthly events are seeing the most significant changes. \r\n\r\nMonthly events will now begin at 11am and end at 6pm, a few hours earlier than at current; but wait, there''s more! The evenings will now be dedicated to a different event every month. From bowling to buffets, these optional extras will provide a new dimension to meets, for those who desire a little bit more variety in exchange for a little bit more cost. \r\n\r\nMonthly meets will also now operate on a schedule, running on the penultimate Saturday of every month unless otherwise stated. Hopefully this will mean more consistent spaces between meets, and the ability to plan them well ahead of time. (We can dream, Harold!)\r\n\r\n<h2>An event expansion</h2>\r\n\r\nAs well as changing how monthlies are operated, we are also introducing new meet types and making others (such as the rare "one-shot" meets) more frequent. \r\n\r\nWe are also expanding our borders and plan to hold more events outside of Bristol city centre. Hawaii is unfortunately unlikely.\r\n\r\n<h2>A staff switcharoo</h2>\r\n\r\nMore staff are being taken on board and more meets will be operated by different individuals. \r\n\r\nInternal decision making is also being drastically altered. No longer will Grey serve as your sole lord and saviour, as there will now be three demi-gods who serve as equal leaders of the organisation - deciding once-and-for-all the rules, operations, and just who is best pony. <small>It''s totally Rainbow Dash.</small> \r\n\r\nThe operating policies for social media, finances, competitions, advertising and marketing are all being altered to be more effectively utilised and to better benefit you - the community. \r\n\r\nWe think we''ve had a good year, and hope you''ve had one too. We look forward to seeing you in 2014!', 'Resolutions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '191-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-25 12:11:21', '2014-03-25 12:11:21', '', 191, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/191-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(193, 1, '2014-03-25 12:18:03', '2014-03-25 12:18:03', 'Hey folks, Grey here with a little update for ya. \r\n\r\nAs you may have heard, as of <a href="/meet/for-whom-the-bell-tolls/">the meet last weekend</a>, I have retired from running meets. It is my belief that there needs to be a change to bring new and different ideas to the meet table&mdash;and I don''t think I should be the man to do it. \r\n\r\nMeets are still going to happen of course, but I''m not going to be the one running most of them. I am staying in my position as designer, developer, treasurer, and on the Bristol Bronies committee of awesome that was created <a href="/news/resolutions/">in January</a>I''m just not going to be the one trying to herd cats around Bristol. \r\n\r\nI leave in my stead a prosperous organisation, defined processes, and meets more frequent and popular than ever before. We have many more things planned for the future stillincluding yet another new website)and trust me, they''ll be awesome. ', 'Retiring behind the scenes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'retiring-behind-the-scenes', '', '', '2014-03-25 12:19:20', '2014-03-25 12:19:20', '', 0, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/?post_type=news&#038;p=193', 0, 'news', '', 0),
(194, 1, '2014-03-25 12:19:20', '2014-03-25 12:19:20', 'Hey folks, Grey here with a little update for ya. \r\n\r\nAs you may have heard, as of <a href="/meet/for-whom-the-bell-tolls/">the meet last weekend</a>, I have retired from running meets. It is my belief that there needs to be a change to bring new and different ideas to the meet table&mdash;and I don''t think I should be the man to do it. \r\n\r\nMeets are still going to happen of course, but I''m not going to be the one running most of them. I am staying in my position as designer, developer, treasurer, and on the Bristol Bronies committee of awesome that was created <a href="/news/resolutions/">in January</a>I''m just not going to be the one trying to herd cats around Bristol. \r\n\r\nI leave in my stead a prosperous organisation, defined processes, and meets more frequent and popular than ever before. We have many more things planned for the future stillincluding yet another new website)and trust me, they''ll be awesome. ', 'Retiring behind the scenes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-25 12:19:20', '2014-03-25 12:19:20', '', 193, 'http://bristolbronies.dev/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
